```{=html}
<section class="fig-layout">
  <!-- Image -->
  <div class="fig-image">
    <img src="images/farmer.webp" alt="Farmer Registration" />
  </div>

  <!-- FIG Concept Text -->
  <div class="fig-text">
    <section id="fig-concept" class="fig-card" data-lang="en" aria-label="FIG concept section">
      <!-- language toggle -->
      <div class="lang-toggle" role="tablist" aria-label="language toggle">
        <button class="lang-btn active" data-set-lang="en" role="tab" aria-selected="true">english</button>
        <button class="lang-btn" data-set-lang="ml" role="tab" aria-selected="false">เดฎเดฒเดฏเดพเดณเด</button>
      </div>

      <!-- english -->
      <article class="lang lang-en" lang="en" aria-live="polite">
        <h2>what is fig?</h2>
        <p><strong>fig (farm in grid)</strong> is a highly secure and trusted platform where any farmer can register for free. after registration, the fig team completes verification. once verified, the farmer receives a <strong>login and password</strong> and a <strong>permanent fig qr code</strong>.</p>

        <p>when someone scans this permanent qr code, they can view the farmerโs verified profile: contact details, photos of the farm, cultivation practices, certifications, and more. for every batch of produce sold, the farmer can easily add batch-specific details (harvest date, variety, inputs used, location, quantity, etc.) so buyers can trace each batch to its origin.</p>

        <div class="fig-callout" role="note">
          <strong>permanent qr code usage:</strong> the same qr can be <u>printed on product labels</u>, <u>shared digitally</u>, or <u>displayed in shops and markets</u>. it always points to the farmerโs fig profile and the latest batch records.
        </div>

        <h3>why use fig?</h3>
        <ul class="fig-benefits">
          <li><strong>free, verified identity:</strong> farmers join at no cost; profiles are verified by the fig team to build trust.</li>
          <li><strong>one qr for life:</strong> a permanent code thatโs easy to print on labels, packs, or display boards.</li>
          <li><strong>batch-level traceability:</strong> record details for each batch in minutes; buyers can see what they are purchasing.</li>
          <li><strong>market visibility:</strong> a clean public profile with photos, practices, and certifications boosts reach and credibility.</li>
          <li><strong>consumer confidence:</strong> scanning reveals authentic, up-to-date data from figโs secure database.</li>
          <li><strong>fair trade and branding:</strong> transparent origin stories help justify price and build loyal customers.</li>
          <li><strong>organization ready:</strong> cooperatives, fpos, and ngos can manage and showcase networks of verified farmers.</li>
          <li><strong>security and control:</strong> login-based updates; farmers control what they publish while fig safeguards data.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <!-- malayalam -->
      <article class="lang lang-ml" lang="ml" aria-live="polite">
